  "doc_id": "50524",
  "text": "False lock detection and recovery technique does not remove ambiguity but rather checks false lock. The most representative detection and recovery technique is referred to as bumpjumping technique [CITATION_1] . This technique employs the traditional ambiguous code tracking loop and constantly check whether this loop is locked on the main peak of BOC ACF. To do so, bump-jumping technique uses two additional correlators located at the theoretical location of the two highest side peaks, as shown in Figure 5 .",
